<paragraph id="490D36ABFFBBBF219A5DF845FF5E752B" blockId="25.[816,1429,1925,2019]" lastBlockId="26.[159,772,220,1514]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">
The records of 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFBBBF229D11F845FB0D71B5" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1050,1193,1959,1985]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFBBBF229D11F845FB0D71B5" box="[1050,1193,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species for 
<collectingRegion id="8B76F849FFBBBF229C43F845FCEB7197" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
are not consistent among previous studies. 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFBBBF219C61F82BFE9F7682" author="VAN STRIEN, N. J." firstAuthor="van Strien" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="25" pageNumber="437" refId="ref28803" refString="VAN STRIEN, N. J. 1996. The checklist mammal fauna of the Gunung Leuser National Park. Pp. 133 - 203, in Leuser: a Sumatran sanctuary (C. P. VAN SCHAIK and J. SUPRIATNA, eds.). Yayasan Bina Sains Hayati Indonesia, Depok, iv + 348 pp." type="book" year="1996">van Strien (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF21987DFF3EFDCD7682" author="Suyanto" box="[374,617,220,246]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Suyanto" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28408" refString="SUYANTO, A., M. YONEDA, I. MARYANTO, MAHARADATUNKAMSI, and J. SUGARDJITO. 1998. Checklist of the mammals of Indonesia: scientific name and distribution area table in Indonesia including CITES, IUCN and Indonesian category for conservation. LIPI-JICA, Bogor, vii + 34 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Suyanto 
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF2198D4FF3EFDBE7682" box="[479,538,220,246]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
(1998
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219B7CFF3EFD177682" author="Suyanto" box="[631,691,220,246]" firstAuthor="Suyanto" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28464" refString="SUYANTO, A., M. YONEDA, I. MARYANTO, MAHARADATUNKAMSI, and J. SUGARDJITO. 2002. Checklist of the mammals of Indonesia: scientific name and distribution area table in Indonesia including CITES, IUCN and Indonesian category for conservation, 2 nd edition. LIPI-JICA-PHKA, Bogor, vii + 63 pp." type="book" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
) listed three species for the island: 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B17FF1CFD6B776C" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1835" box="[540,719,254,280]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fuliginosus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B17FF1CFD6B776C" box="[540,719,254,280]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. fuliginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219994FEC3FEF0774F" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[159,340,289,315]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219994FEC3FEF0774F" box="[159,340,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. schreibersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the studies, but see 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219B70FEC3FF7A7729" author="Tian" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Tian" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" pagination="303 - 311" refId="ref28636" refString="TIAN, L., B. LIANGI, K. MAEDA, W. METZNER, and S. ZHANG. 2004. Molecular studies on the classification of Miniopterus schreibersii (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) inferred from mitochondrial cytochrome b sequences. Folia Zoologica, 53: 303 - 311." type="journal article" year="2004">
Tian 
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219BB7FEC3FD58774F" box="[700,764,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2004
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF2199F8FEA1FE287729" baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[243,396,323,349]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnater">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF2199F8FEA1FE287729" box="[243,396,323,349]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. magnater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF2198DBFEA1FDF07729" box="[464,596,323,349]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF2198DBFEA1FDF07729" box="[464,596,323,349]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the records of 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219810FE87FE39770B" box="[283,413,357,383]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219810FE87FE39770B" box="[283,413,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(also see 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219B1BFE87FD5F770B" author="Whitten" box="[528,763,357,383]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Whitten" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28927" refString="WHITTEN, A. J., S. J. DAMNIK, J. ANWAR, and N. HISYAM. 2000. Chapter Ten: caves. Pp. 313 - 336, in The ecology of Sumatra, 1 st periplus edition. Tuttle Publishing, North Clarendo, xxxix + 478 pp." type="book" year="2000">
Whitten 
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B7DFE87FD14770B" box="[630,688,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
) were not included in subsequent reviews (
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219BBAFE65FEE077B0" author="Corbet and Hill" firstAuthor="Corbet" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref25099" refString="CORBET, G. B., and J. E. HILL. 1992. The mammals of the Indomalayan Region: a systematic review. Natural History Museum Publications, Oxford, 488 pp." type="book" year="1992">Corbet and Hill 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF21985BFE48FDA877B0" author="Simmons" box="[336,524,426,452]" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref27949" refString="SIMMONS, N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. Pp. 312 - 529, in Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference, 3 rd edition (D. E. WILSON and D. M. REEDER, eds.). The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, xxxv + 2142 pp." type="book" year="2005">Simmons, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219B13FE48FD5A77B0" author="Boitani" box="[536,766,426,452]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Boitani" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref24868" refString="BOITANI, L., I. CATULLO, M. MARZETTI, M. MASI, M. RULLI, and S. SAVINI. 2006. The Southeast Asian mammal databank. A tool for conservation and monitoring of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia. Instituto di Ecologia Applicata, Rome. Available at www. ieaitaly. org / samd /." type="book" year="2006">
Boitani 
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B7DFE48FD1577B0" box="[630,689,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219994FE2EFE917792" author="IUCN" box="[159,309,460,486]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref26437" refString="IUCN 2013. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2013.1. &lt;www. iucnredlist. org&gt;. Last accessed on 4 th July 2013." type="book" year="2013">IUCN, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). An additional species, 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B58FE2EFD457792" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[595,737,460,486]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B58FE2EFD457792" box="[595,737,460,486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is listed for 
<collectingRegion id="8B76F849FFB8BF219805FE0CFED4747C" box="[270,368,494,520]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
by a few recent studies (
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219B84FE0CFEAA745E" author="Boitani" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Boitani" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref24868" refString="BOITANI, L., I. CATULLO, M. MARZETTI, M. MASI, M. RULLI, and S. SAVINI. 2006. The Southeast Asian mammal databank. A tool for conservation and monitoring of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia. Instituto di Ecologia Applicata, Rome. Available at www. ieaitaly. org / samd /." type="book" year="2006">
Boitani 
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219BE5FE0CFF19745E" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219815FDF2FE1C745E" author="IUCN" box="[286,440,528,554]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref26437" refString="IUCN 2013. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2013.1. &lt;www. iucnredlist. org&gt;. Last accessed on 4 th July 2013." type="book" year="2013">IUCN, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Due to similarities in appearance, the classification of 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B06FDD1FD387439" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[525,668,563,589]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B06FDD1FD387439" box="[525,668,563,589]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain, which makes species identification in the field difficult (
<bibRefCitation id="2D234B5AFFB8BF219847FD95FE5074E5" author="Francis" box="[332,500,631,657]" firstAuthor="Francis" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref25558" refString="FRANCIS, C. M. 2008. A guide to mammals of Southeast Asia. Princeton University Press, Princeton, NJ, 392 pp." type="book" year="2008">Francis, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, we recognize three morphologically distinct species in our samples, and assign names to three of the four known species (see species accounts below). Further studies of craniodental measurements and genetic relationships are necessary to confirm our identifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="490D36ABFFB8BF2199CEFC85FACF743F" blockId="26.[159,772,220,1514]" lastBlockId="26.[816,1429,220,587]" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF2199CEFC85FE6775F5" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[197,451,871,897]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF2199CEFC85FE6775F5" box="[197,451,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the smallest of the three recognized species from our study area. Comparing with known 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219838FC4EFE6675B2" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[307,450,940,966]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219838FC4EFE6675B2" box="[307,450,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Sunda shelf, the forearm length, body mass, and tibia length of the bat overlapped largely with 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B20FC12FD1A727E" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[555,702,1008,1034]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B20FC12FD1A727E" box="[555,702,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other localities, but were smaller than all other 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219994FBD7FE8A723B" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[159,302,1077,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219994FBD7FE8A723B" box="[159,302,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<tableCitation id="04300310FFB8BF2198A5FBD7FDB1723B" box="[430,533,1077,1103]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="26.[159,172,1595,1616]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="TABLE 4. Selected external traits and distribution of known Miniopterus species on the Sunda Shelf and this study. FA — forearm length (mm), BM — body mass (g), TB — tibia length (mm). Data in parentheses denote samples of this study" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/1DCD6623FFB8BF219994F9D9FB777019" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" tableUuid="1DCD6623FFB8BF219994F9D9FB777019">Table 4</tableCitation>
). Individuals were characterized by orange-yellow and flesh-colored skin of the face and tragus, which was not observed in the other two 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219864FB79FE5A72C1" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[367,510,1179,1205]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219864FB79FE5A72C1" box="[367,510,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in our study. Similar coloration is seen in 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B24FB5CFD1372AC" box="[559,695,1214,1240]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B24FB5CFD1372AC" box="[559,695,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. medius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="31A5763BFFB8BF219823FB02FE30728E" box="[296,404,1248,1274]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
but not in 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219B22FB02FD19728E" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[553,701,1248,1274]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219B22FB02FD19728E" box="[553,701,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Borneo (J. Senawi, personal communication). However, coloration is seldom used as a diagnostic trait to identify cave-roosting insectivorous bats in Southeast Asia because variations in color among individuals and geographic populations are commonly found in many species. Although this color pattern is stable in our samples, in the present study, we assign this species as 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219D6CFF3EFB5C7682" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[1127,1272,220,246]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219D6CFF3EFB5C7682" box="[1127,1272,220,246]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
solely based upon the body size. Individuals were recorded from caves in Way Canguk Forest and were found using the same roosts as 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219D2AFEA0FA897728" baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[1057,1325,322,348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnater">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219D2AFEA0FA897728" box="[1057,1325,322,348]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus magnater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219C4AFEA0FCCA770A" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219C4AFEA0FCCA770A" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219A8EFE86FBDA770A" baseAuthorityName="van Strien" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[901,1150,356,382]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219A8EFE86FBDA770A" box="[901,1150,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Rhinolophus lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219D8DFE86FB45770A" box="[1158,1249,356,382]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219D8DFE86FB45770A" box="[1158,1249,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219DF3FE86FC3777D4" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cervinus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219DF3FE86FC3777D4" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Hipposideros cervinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219AD0FE64FB0B77D4" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[987,1199,390,416]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219AD0FE64FB0B77D4" box="[987,1199,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Myotis horsfieldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the study area, 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219A3BFE4BFC6577B7" authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[816,961,425,451]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219A3BFE4BFC6577B7" box="[816,961,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from other known 
<taxonomicName id="8EB24D28FFB8BF219A86FE29FBB87791" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[909,1052,459,485]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7BC6EAB9FFB8BF219A86FE29FBB87791" box="[909,1052,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the skin color and the smaller size (
<tableCitation id="04300310FFB8BF219D0DFE0FFBC37473" box="[1030,1127,493,519]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="10.[99,112,501,522]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="TABLE 2. Measurements of nine external traits of 52 bat species. FA — forearm length, BM — body mass, HB — head and body length, TL — tail length, TB — tibia length, HF — hind foot length, TU — thumb length: EL — ear length, TR — tragus length. Numbers denote minimum and maximum, and sample size; values in parentheses indicate measurements of specimens of this study; ‘ – ’: data not available. BMs for specimens were taken in the field. All measurements in mm, except for BM (in g)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/1DCD6623FFA8BF319968FE17FA147437" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" tableUuid="1DCD6623FFA8BF319968FE17FA147437">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Our record is the first record of this species in BBSL and extends the distribution in Sumatra from the north to the south.
</paragraph>
